728368f-a.folder: Arthur Kill Road & Woodrow Road, Staten Island, NY
728368f-a.original_title: Richmond: Arthur Kill Road - Woodrow Road
728368f-a.text:
1260 Arthur K1ll Road, adjoining the S.W. corner of Woodrow Road. This house belonged to Dr. D. A. Edgar in 1874, and later (1898) to David J. Tysen. In 1907 it was owned by Wm. Fitzgerald and in 1917 by David J. Tysen. The dates refer to maps on which the names of the
owners are recorded.
April 9, 1927
P. L. Sperr

728369f-a.folder: Arthur Kill Road & Woodrow Road, Staten Island, NY
728369f-a.original_title: Richmond: Arthur Kill Road - Woodrow Road
728369f-a.text:
1281 Arthur Kill Road, north side, west of Woodrow Road, showing the home and barns of Wms H. Colgan, a local farmer. For additional views of the Colgan farm see "Farming on Staten Island'
views.
January 31, 1931
Views 1, 2, 3
P. L. Soerr

729959f-a.folder: Woodrow Road & Arthur Kill Road, Staten Island, NY
729959f-a.original_title: Richmond: Woodrow Road - Arthur Kill Road
729959f-a.text:
(1)
Woodrow Road, east side, 800 feet south of Arthur Kill Road, showing the D. V. H. Floyd House (Butlere 1853 map). From 1874 to 1898 the maps show it to have been the H. Barger house, and from 1907 to 1917 the Dierauf house. This is the
north side of the dwelling.
April 9, 1927
P. L. Sperr
(2)
Looking north and showing the south side of
the house.
April 9, 1927
P. L. Sperr
